      "markdown_content": "**Imaging Analysis Report**\n\n**Patient ID:** MDT2024001\n\n**Date of Report:** October 26, 2024\n\n**Reporting Radiologist:** Imaging Analysis Agent\n\n\n**1. Technical Assessment**\n\n* **Study Quality:**  All imaging studies (chest x-ray, CT chest, PET-CT) are of adequate technical quality for interpretation.  The PET-CT demonstrates good image quality with appropriate uptake and background activity.\n\n* **Comparison with Prior Imaging:** No prior imaging studies are available for comparison.\n\n* **Technical Limitations:** None significant.\n\n\n**2. Clinical Findings**\n\n* **Primary Lesion Characteristics:** A 3.8 x 3.2 cm spiculated mass is identified in the right upper lobe on CT chest.  The mass demonstrates intense FDG avidity on PET-CT (SUVmax 12.4), consistent with malignancy.  The spiculated margins on CT suggest an aggressive growth pattern.\n\n* **Disease Extent:**  The CT chest demonstrates multiple enlarged right hilar and mediastinal lymph nodes. These nodes are also FDG-avid on PET-CT (SUVmax 8.2), indicating metastatic involvement. No evidence of distant metastases is seen on CT chest or PET-CT.\n\n* **Secondary Findings:** Mild emphysematous changes are noted in the upper lobes on CT.  Right supraclavicular lymphadenopathy is reported on physical exam, although this is not directly visualized on the provided imaging.\n\n\n**3. Staging Assessment**\n\nBased on the imaging findings, the following TNM staging is proposed:\n\n* **T:** T2 (\u22653cm primary tumor)\n* **N:** N2 (Mediastinal lymph node involvement)\n* **M:** M0 (No distant metastases)\n\n**Stage IIIA (according to the 8th TNM edition)**\n\n**Size Measurements:**\n\n* Primary tumor: 3.8 x 3.2 cm\n\n**Progression Criteria:** The presence of mediastinal lymph node involvement excludes stages I and II.  The absence of distant metastases excludes stages IIIB and IV.\n\n**4. Anatomical Considerations:**\n\nThe primary tumor is located in the right upper lobe, clo