psychosocial support, should be an integral part of the treatment plan.\n\n\n**4. Evidence Level:**\n\n* **Strength of Recommendations:**  The recommendations are based on strong evidence from clinical trials and established guidelines for the treatment of lung adenocarcinoma with KRAS G12C mutations and high PD-L1 expression.  Specific treatment choices (KRAS G12C inhibitor vs. immunotherapy) will depend on individual patient factors and should be discussed within the MDT setting.\n\n* **Quality of Evidence:** The evidence for KRAS G12C inhibitors and PD-1/PD-L1 inhibitors in lung adenocarcinoma is high, based on multiple randomized controlled trials demonstrating significant improvements in progression-free survival and overall survival.\n\n* **Guideline Sources:**  Recommendations are based on NCCN Guidelines for Lung Cancer, ASCO guidelines, and relevant published clinical trials.  Specific trial references will be provided within the MDT discussion and documented in the patient's chart.\n\n\n**5. Clinical Trial Considerations:** The patient's profile makes her a strong candidate for several clinical trials investigating novel combinations of targeted therapies and immunotherapies for advanced-stage lung adenocarcinoma with KRAS mutations.  The MDT should discuss the potential benefits and risks of participating in a clinical trial.\n\n**6. Documentation of Deviations:**  No deviations from standard practice are anticipated at this time.  All decisions will be made in consultation with a multidisciplinary team, and any deviations from standard protocols will be clearly documented and justified in the patient's medical record.  The treatment plan will be individualized based on the patient's specific characteristics and preferences.\n\n**Note:** This analysis is based on the provided data.  Further investigations, such as additional imaging, and more detailed assessment of the patient's performance status, are necessary before finalizing a treatment plan.  This i