rom surgery and chemotherapy to targeted therapy or palliative care.  Given the potential severity of the condition and the patient's age and comorbidities, shared decision-making with the patient and her family is paramount.  A thorough discussion regarding prognosis and treatment goals is essential.\n\n**Limitations and Uncertainties:** The diagnosis remains presumptive pending further investigations. The information provided is incomplete; more detailed information on the patient\u2019s history, family history, and imaging results is needed for a definitive diagnosis and treatment plan.  A complete medication list is also necessary.\n\n\n**Recommendations:**\n\n1.  Urgent chest CT scan with contrast.\n2.  Bronchoscopy with biopsy for definitive diagnosis.\n3.  Multidisciplinary team (MDT) meeting to discuss findings and formulate a treatment plan.\n4.  Thorough assessment of performance status using validated scales (e.g., ECOG).\n5.  Detailed discussion with the patient and her family regarding prognosis and treatment options.\n\n\nThis analysis provides a preliminary assessment based on the available data.  Further information is needed to refine the diagnosis and treatment plan.  All recommendations are subject to change based on further clinical findings.",
